The paper deals with pattern discovery in large-scale geo-spatiotemporal data, which involves handling and analyzing large amounts of data. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DB (databases) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a new framework for pattern discovery, which involves machine learning and data mining techniques, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.AI (artificial intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the exploration of influential patterns, which involves information retrieval and ranking, suggesting that it could belong to the cs.IR (information retrieval) sub-category. The paper deals with spatiotemporal data, which involves handling and analyzing data over time and space, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.SI (social and information networks) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the identification of patterns and insights, which involves statistical analysis and modeling, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.LG (machine learning) sub-category.
